title: llvm test failing

labels.name: A-LLVM
labels.description: Area: Code generation parts specific to LLVM. Both correctness bugs and optimization-related issues.

body:
What I did:
````bash
cd src/llvm
mkdir tests
cd tests
cmake ..
make check -j 4
````

What I got:
````
[100%] Running the LLVM regression tests
FAIL: LLVM-Unit :: Analysis/./AnalysisTests/TargetLibraryInfoTest.ValidProto (1062 of 23293)
******************** TEST 'LLVM-Unit :: Analysis/./AnalysisTests/TargetLibraryInfoTest.ValidProto' FAILED ********************

/home/matthias/RUST/rust/src/llvm/unittests/Analysis/TargetLibraryInfoTest.cpp:529: Failure

Expected: true
/home/matthias/RUST/rust/src/llvm/unittests/Analysis/TargetLibraryInfoTest.cpp:529: Failure

Expected: true
````

How bad is this?
